South African-born comedian Trevor Noah became the kids favourite African personality after he was crowned with the African Star Award at the 2017 Nickelodeon Kids Choice Awards.The 30th edition of the star-studded award ceremony was held at USC s Galen Centre in Los Angeles, California, on Saturday.The ace comedian beat fellow South Africans Pearl Thusi and Wayde van Niekerk, as well as his Nigerian counterparts, Yemi Alade and Funke Akindele Bello and Kenyan Hollywood actress, Lupita Nyong o to walk away with the coveted orange blimp after kids across the world voted for the Born a Crime author.The win comes hot on the heels of Time Magazine s Next Generation Leaders top 10 list last week praised the comedian as the master of the eloquent Trump-takedown . In February, The Daily Show posted increased viewership figures owing its streak to its coverage of Trump s inauguration as US president and other political events.This year Nickelodeon, the number-one kids network targeting children between 7-17 years with more than 1.2 million viewers in total a day, celebrates its 37th year.Winners are selected by Nickelodeon viewers through voting on the channel s website as well as social media and text messaging.The 30th edition of the awards was hosted by WWE athlete John Cena with performances from Little Mix, Machine Gun Kelly and Camila Cabello and appearances by Nick Cannon, Ellen DeGeneres and Kevin Hart among others.SIYABONGA SITHOLE